2.1 MCMC

k <- 3 #number of cases
data <- matrix(c(70, 50, 30, 50, 7, 5, 3, 5, 10, 0, 0, 10), 
               nrow=k, ncol=4, byrow=T)
data
     [,1] [,2] [,3] [,4]
[1,]   70   50   30   50
[2,]    7    5    3    5
[3,]   10    0    0   10
h <- data[,1]
f <- data[,2]
MI <- data[,3]
CR <- data[,4]
s <- h + MI
n <- f + CR

data <- list("h", "f", "k", "s", "n") # to be passed on to JAGS
myinits <- list(
  list(d = rep(0,k), c = rep(0,k)))  

# parameters to be monitored:   
parameters <- c("d", "c", "thetah", "thetaf")

model_text <- "
# Signal Detection Theory
model{
  for (i in 1:k){
  # Observed counts
    h[i] ~ dbin(thetah[i],s[i])
    f[i] ~ dbin(thetaf[i],n[i])
    
    # Reparameterization Using Equal-Variance Gaussian SDT
    thetah[i] <- phi(d[i]/2-c[i])
    thetaf[i] <- phi(-d[i]/2-c[i])
    
    # These Priors over Discriminability and Bias Correspond 
    # to Uniform Priors over the Hit and False Alarm Rates
    d[i] ~ dnorm(0,0.5)
    c[i] ~ dnorm(0,2)
  }
}"

samples <- jags(data, inits=myinits, parameters,
                 model.file = textConnection(model_text),
                 n.chains=1, n.iter=10000,
         n.burnin=1, n.thin=1, DIC=T)
